column5: Finally got around to making my video actually made 6 separate days. The videos are at my blog walleyewarrior.blogspot.com. I am posting our best day which was Wednesday over 250 walleyes with an amazing 70% over 20 inches. Our biggest on the week was 27 what an amazing drive to lake. Just gets better every year

Great videos. Thanks for posting. I'm headed there this July for the first time. I'm taking three of my kids with me and they are already talking about it. Although I'm not really looking forward to driving 1,300 miles by myself. Twice.
MRSimon, the drive will be worth it and that a great time of the year to be on that lake.
Thanks for great video. Im going to have to add that place to the bucket list.

Agreed drive there is worth it everything north of the bridge into Canada is really great scenery especially along Lake Superior. Hardest part of going to OSulliivans Rainbow is getting a cabin they are seriously booked but by putting your name into their list sooner or later something comes up
